<br>
I am a US Marine currently based in California. I have served overseas on Embassy Duty in Spain. It was a truly great experience. I am saying this to start out that I am an American and I do not hate Europeans.<br>
<br>
I am in the Vale guild right now as we form an entire new guild from the people with set guidelines, defined roles, and other such planning. This seems to be currently the only US exclusive guild right now. Not to say we wouldnt accept Europeans (in fact we have at least one that I know of) it's just that we are starting to focus on raids more and it is essential that every is there, prompt, etc.. You all know how it works probably much better then I do.<br>
<br>
This thread was started as a joke :Þ But I have been thinking sorta on this line of thought as a few threads have backlashed at each other. <br>
<br>
In answer to your question there are several hindrances to being an uber guild on this server as an American guild.<br>
<br>
First: Overcrowded with high-level characters making it hard for us to get a spawn during our time because it is most likely killed a few hours after a patch or respawn.<br>
<br>
Second: This one I believe to be the biggest reason. No teamwork with the other guilds. That's right noone on this server trusts anyone else. They would not mind trying a mob and get slaughtered 16 times as long as it is for themselves alone. Ask them to do a pickup raid and the excuse is that noone wants to die. That is just plain untrust of everyone else and is sad.<br>
<br>
Third: Number. Yeah I am not saying to zerg but there is a definate benefit in more number and some things just cannot be done without much larger numbers then we have without very difficult planning and possible multiple failures.<br>
<br>
Fourth: There are more Americans out there that are not guilded and will probably not be with us for the simple fact that some want to be uber and that is not our goal and so they dont see any future with us at all which is quite sad. Our goal is to have fun and raid the end-game mobs. This is not something to do to be uber or because you are. This is something to do because you can and it is a lot of fun. If they had a scripted event like the 10th Ring War in say FV with Iksars coming from Swamp of No Hope you better believe I would be there even if no good loot dropped due to the sheer fact that it would be a ton of fun and would be what I started playing the game for.<br>
<br>
I guess I am done rambling and would like to see more constructive posts and maybe even some of those people that seem to be so set against us Americans to give us a chance I know I have grouped with a lot of Europeans and cannot say anything about them bad as a continent at all just based on a few people or for even that goes a whole guild. Some guilds in all countries have poor members which make the whole guild look back but you shouldn't believe that everyone that has ever grouped with them or comes from the same geographical region is automatically the same type of person.<br>
<br>
Adar Rahl<br>
Level 60 Paladin<br>
Sergeant in the US Marines <p></p><span class=m><i></i></span><hr size=1>   &nbsp;&nbsp;<a href=http://pub44.ezboard.com/fantoniusbaylecommunitycentrefrm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=183.topic&index=58><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/ultimate/reply.gif border=0 width=20 height=20 alt="reply to this message" align=absmiddle></a>   <br><br></td></tr></table></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#003366><td colspan=2><table cellpadding=8 cellspacing=0 width=100%><tr><td nowrap width=20% valign=top><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub44.ezboard.com/uauvdaroakenmist.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Auvdar OakenMist</A> </span><br><BR><img src=http://ashran.freeservers.com/r-drgn1.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60><br> <span class=usertitle>Duck of Doom</span><br>  Posts: <b>109</b><br></td><td valign=top align=left class=m width=80%><span class=m><font color=#6699F>Posted: 2/25/02 1:10:49 am</font>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</span><br><span class=title> Re: lala</span><hr size=1> Shatze, EVERYTHING you just said could be said about Canadians, Europeans, Japanese, etc. Point here is that everyone is pointing the finger at Americans, ignorant of the fact that their own nationality has the same problems. And I'll say it again, all these things are a HUMAN, read my words, H U M A N, trait, not a National trait. In other words, if ONE nation shows this trait, more than likely other nations will and do show this trait.<br>
